article_title: White House Woos Young People for Health Insurance Sign-Ups
article_text:
Supporters of the Affordable Care Act are conducting a late push to persuade so-called “young invincibles”—youthful Americans who consider themselves immune to illness—and other key groups to sign up for health insurance in advance of Sunday night’s deadline.

The White House cranked up its online outreach for health-care enrollees this week with a video from the website BuzzFeed featuring President Barack Obama practicing his jump...
